Or, it could be because you have to set a higher value on =
maxFieldLength in
the IndexWriter you use.

>From the javadoc (IndexWriter):

"public int maxFieldLength

The maximum number of terms that will be indexed for a single field in =
a
document. This limits the amount of memory required for indexing, so =
that
collections with very large files will not crash the indexing process =
by
running out of memory.=20

By default, no more than 10,000 terms will be indexed for a field."


