Hello,

I'm using Lucene (1.2RC5) and, when indexing, I include a field called =
"headline" using the following line of code in the document I create to =
use for indexing:

      addField("headline", root.elementText("headline"), true, true, =
true, doc);

When I search on headline:term1, it works just fine.  But I've noticed =
that if I query using, for example,=20

        headline:"on the job"

I will get returned all items that have the term 'job' in their =
headline.

I presume I've overlooked something and would appreciate any suggestions =
on what that might be.

Regards,

Terry Steichen


